OL,3,CMuseum struggling to 'keep the lights
OL,4,Con' due to 'astronomic' energy bills
OL,6,FIt reopened in 2022 after a #1.6m
OL,7,Fredevelopment scheme partly funded by
OL,8,Fa Heritage Lottery Fund grant, with
OL,9,Fthe remainder of the money coming
OL,10,Fmainly in grants from other charitable
OL,11,Fbodies, and an annual grant from
OL,12,FLlandudno Town Council.
OL,14,FThe museum aims to raise #80,000 by
OL,15,FOctober to keep the lights on.
OL,17,FJudith Phillips, a trustee at the
OL,18,Fmuseum for 12 years, said "this is the
OL,19,Fworst crisis the museum has had to
OL,20,Fface" in that time.
